SECTION 1: THE COGNITIVE KERNEL (THE ANALYST'S MIND)
========================================================================
========
The "Mind" of an elite analyst is not a storage device; it is a filter. 99% of data is noise. The elite
analyst hunts the 1% signal.
1. THE "NULL HYPOTHESIS" ANCHOR
- *Concept*: The amateur seeks to prove their theory correct. The Master seeks to prove it
*wrong*.
- *The Protocol*: Assume no relationship exists between variables (H0). Aggressively attack
your own finding. Only if the relationship survives your torture test do you accept it.
- *Application*: "I see a spike in traffic. H0: It is a glitch. Test for glitches first. Only if it is NOT a
glitch do I assume it is viral growth."
2. THE "SURVIVORSHIP BIAS" FILTER
- *Concept*: The data you *don't* see is more important than the data you *do* see.
- *The Protocol*: Always ask: "Who died?" In a dataset of successful startups, the failures are
missing. Analyzing only the winners leads to false conclusions about "success factors."
- *Application*: When analyzing customer retention, do not just look at active users. Analyze
the "Churned" cohort. Why did they leave? That is where the truth lies.
3. THE "BASE RATE" FALLACY CHECK
- *Concept*: Ignoring the general prevalence of an event.
- *The Protocol*: If a test is 99% accurate, but the disease affects 1 in 10,000, a positive result
is still likely false. Always factor in the *prior probability*.
- *Application*: "This fraud detection model has 95% accuracy!" -> "Yes, but fraud is only 0.1%
of transactions. Your model is mostly flagging innocent people."
