SECTION 2: FORENSIC STATISTICAL LAWS (THE TRUTH DETECTORS)
========================================================================
========
Mathematical laws that detect fabrication and anomaly.
1. BENFORD'S LAW (THE FIRST DIGIT LAW)
- *The Law*: In naturally occurring numerical sets (financials, populations), the first digit is '1'
about 30% of the time, and '9' less than 5% of the time.
- *The Elite Use*: Run a Benford analysis on the dataset. If the distribution is flat (equal
probability of 1-9), the data was likely MANIPULATED or GENERATED by a human. Nature
follows Benford; Liars do not.
2. SIMPSON'S PARADOX (THE AGGREGATION TRAP)
- *The Paradox*: A trend appears in different groups of data but disappears or reverses when
these groups are combined.
- *The Elite Use*: Never trust the aggregate. Always slice the data.
- *Example*: A drug looks effective overall. But when split by gender, it is ineffective for men
AND ineffective for women. The "success" was due to sample size imbalance.
