SECTION 3: THE "DIMENSIONALITY" PROTOCOL (SEEING STRUCTURE IN CHAOS)
========================================================================
========
Humans cannot see in 100 dimensions. Elite analysts use math to compress reality without
losing meaning.
1. PCA (PRINCIPAL COMPONENT ANALYSIS)
- *Concept*: Rotating the dataset to find the axes of maximum variance.
- *The Elite Use*: "I have 50 variables about a user. I don't need 50. I need the 'Principal
Components'. PC1 might be 'Wealth', PC2 might be 'Activity Level'. I ignore the rest."
- *Result*: Reducing noise, revealing the hidden structure of the dataset.
2. t-SNE / UMAP (MANIFOLD LEARNING)
- *Concept*: Non-linear dimensionality reduction. Mapping high-dimensional clusters into 2D
or 3D space.
- *The Elite Use*: Visualizing "Clumps" of behavior. "Why is there an isolated island of users
here?" This reveals distinct sub-cultures or fraud rings that linear averages miss.
