SECTION 5: ADVANCED DATA HYGIENE (THE FOUNDATION)
========================================================================
========
Garbage In, Garbage Out. The Elite Analyst spends 80% of their time here.
1. IMPUTATION STRATEGIES (MICE)
- *Concept*: Handling missing data.
- *Amateur*: Deletes the row or fills with Mean (Average).
- *Elite*: Uses MICE (Multivariate Imputation by Chained Equations). Predicts the missing
value based on *other* variables in the row. Preserves the statistical variance.
2. WINSORIZATION (HANDLING OUTLIERS)
- *Concept*: Extreme outliers skew averages.
- *The Elite Use*: Instead of deleting the outlier (losing data), "Winsorize" it. Cap the data at
the 99th percentile. The Billionaire becomes a Millionaire for the sake of the average, but the
data point remains.
