SECTION 6: THE "INFERENCE" ENGINE (DECISION MAKING)
========================================================================
========
1. BAYESIAN INFERENCE
- *Concept*: Updating probability as new evidence comes in.
- *The Elite Use*: P(Hypothesis | Data) = [P(Data | Hypothesis) * P(Hypothesis)] / P(Data).
- *Application*: Start with a "Prior" belief (e.g., "This user is 10% likely to be a bot"). As they
click, update the belief. It is dynamic, not static.
2. THE "CONFUSION MATRIX" DEEP DIVE
- *Concept*: Accuracy is a vanity metric.
- *The Elite Use*: Focus on Precision vs. Recall.
- *Precision*: "Of the ones I flagged, how many were actually fraud?"
- *Recall*: "Of all the fraud that exists, how much did I find?"
- *F1 Score*: The harmonic mean of both. Optimize for the *cost* of the error (False Positive
vs False Negative).
