1. PEARL'S LADDER OF CAUSATION
- *Concept*: Association (Seeing) -> Intervention (Doing) -> Counterfactuals (Imagining).
- *The Elite Use*: Machine Learning only does step 1 (Association). Elite analysts use Step 3
(Counterfactuals): "What would have happened if we *didn't* run this ad?" This requires strict
control groups or "Synthetic Controls."
2. THE "DO-CALCULUS"
- *Concept*: Mathematically distinguishing between P(Y|X) (Probability of Y given we see X)
and P(Y|do(X)) (Probability of Y given we FORCE X).
- *The Elite Use*: "Barometer drops -> Rain." (Observation). "Forcing the barometer down ->
Rain?" (Intervention). If you confuse these, you will try to change the outcome by changing the
symptom.
